race.comment: Dunkeld's only meeting for the year and if you do plan to have a bet here, make sure you watch the races because it is a sight to behold as probably Victoria's most picturesque venue. MAGNABELLE ROYALE (7) is a filly by Magnus out of Effigy Belle who is at the races for the first time today. Has won her three trials this campaign and looks primed for a big debut performance. FAKE FICTION (5) could not possibly be considered on the debut run, but she did start hard in the market that day and some impressive jumpouts since suggest she's better for that campaign. DON'T DOUBT DOTTIE (4) needs to lift on the debut performance and has a wide gate to contend with but the trials before the first start suggested she's got her fair share of talent and it might be worth giving her one more chance. ZOUIE (10) finished third last time over 1200m at Bairnsdale, beaten 2.25 lengths. This looks like a sterner test than last time but on her best form she is capable of a big performance.
